-- Energy Minister Borloo Says There Are No Plans for French Fuel Rationing
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-10-22T10:38:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/energy-minister-borloo-says-there-are-no-plans-for-french-fuel-rationing.html
French Energy Minister Jean-Louis
Borloo said there are no plans for fuel rationing.  France is importing 120,000 cubic meters of fuel a day and
has 7 million cubic meters of fuel reserves, Borloo told
reporters in Paris.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  